description: Outline application (all matters reserved) for mixed-use redevelopment of the site known as 'Wood Wharf' comprising: Demolition of existing buildings and structures, including dwellings at Lovegrove Walk; The erection of buildings, including tall buildings and basements, comprising: Residential units (Use Class C3); Hotel (C1); Business floorspace (B1); Retail (A1-A5); Community and Leisure (D1 and D2); and, Sui Generis uses. Associated infrastructure, including the creation of structures in Blackwall Basin, Graving Dock, and South Dock; Streets, open spaces, landscaping and public realm; Bridge links;  Car, motorcycle and bicycle parking spaces and servicing spaces;  Utilities including energy centres and electricity substation(s); and other works incidental to the proposed development. (REVISED APPLICATION) [This outline planning application has been amended. A brief description of some of key amendments is below: Removal of 'Swing Plots' the introduction of certainty on the Building Plots that will be residential and the Building Plots that will be commercial. Residential Maximum  the removal of the Swing Plots has resulted in the reduction of the maximum number of residential units that can be delivered from 4,500 to 3,610 units;  Commercial Minimum - the removal of the Swing Plots has resulted in an increase to the minimum quantum of business floorspace from 100,000 sqm to 165,000 sqm (GIA);  Pedestrian Access  further pedestrian access has been committed to in and around Development Zone J; and, Affordable Housing Quantum and Mix the affordable housing offer has been increased.
